Use Python 3.2 (3.1 doesn't work)
configure botconfig.py.example (rename to botconfig.py first)
if desired, configure settings/wolfgame.py to modify game settings
run wolfbot.py

If looking to use the auto-update feature, you need the git shell
download the Git shell at http://git-scm.com/download/
you can clone the repository, or fork it. the IRC service needs to be enabled
Whenever the GitHub commit bot joins and says there's an update, it downloads it
ALLOW_GIT must be set to True in .\settings\wolfgame.py